. Repeat with remaining mixture (makes approx. 16 meatballs) and set Varoma aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Red beans and rice"},{"content":"Insert simmering basket into mixing bowl and weigh rice into it. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and rinse rice until water runs clear, then set aside to drain."},{"content":"Place oil, onion, garlic, carrot and celery into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and sauté <b>1 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add reserved rice and remaining ingredients, except capsicum, kidney beans and spring onions\/shallots. Stir to combine with aid of spatula and cook <b>20 min\/100°C\/\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>15-18 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 2<b>, or until turkey is cooked through. Remove Varoma and transfer meatballs into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and cover to keep warm."},{"content":"Add capsicum and kidney beans and heat <b>3 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>, mixing with aid of spatula."},{"content":"Transfer into thermal serving bowl with meatballs and garnish with spring onions\/shallots before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or <em>Everyday Cookbook <\/em>for the Chicken stock paste recipe.","You can replace the turkey in this recipe with chicken or pork mince."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h","4 portions"]}